Sandusky Junior/Senior High School
August 18 at 6:27 PM ·

The “Lunch and a Book” event is very popular with SHS students. This year, over 20 of our students read The Weight of Our Sky by Hanna Alkaf. Today, some of these students joined students from Carmen Ainsworth in Flint and students from a reservation in South Dakota to discuss this book in a virtual book talk. Thank you to those that make these opportunities possible.

Sandusky Junior/Senior High School
August 18 at 6:27 PM ·

The “Lunch and a Book” event is very popular with SHS students. This year, over 20 of our students read The Weight of Our Sky by Hanna Alkaf. Today, some of these students joined students from Carmen Ainsworth in Flint and students from a reservation in South Dakota to discuss this book in a virtual book talk. Thank you to those that make these opportunities possible.

post_text:
Sandusky Community Schools has a long standing reputation for its strong relationship with the community and doing what is best for its kids. We are proud of our staff, and the quality of education we provide to students.

Tuesday's ballot asks that you continue to support the district with a 2 mill Sinking Fund that will provide money for maintenance projects to the high school, elementary, and grounds.

Please remember that this is not an increase on your taxes, rather the school millage rate will stay the same. This money must be used for projects, and cannot be used for salary increases.

Thank you again for your continued support of our schools as you head to the polls tomorrow.

Mr. Williams will be donating his prize to the elementary! Superintendent Paul Flynn is presenting Mr. Williams with the plaque of recognition that will be displayed in the elementary office.

shared_text:
Sandusky Junior/Senior High School
June 9 at 12:54 PM ·

SHS is excited to announce that we will hold our Class of 2020 Commencement Ceremony on our football field at 7 PM on Thursday, June 25. The date/time of 7 PM on Friday, June 26 has been reserved as a back-up date in case of inclement weather.

We are so pleased that we can now announce this date, but many details still must be planned. These details will be communicated to graduates and their parents by email as well as by US mail as soon as possible.

Once again, congratulations to the SHS Class of 2020!

The Outpost Food Pantry is still open Tuesday’s 9 am - Noon and Wednesday’s 3:00 pm-6:00 pm. However to protect you and our volunteers we will be changing the process up slightly. To help practice social distancing we are asking that you stay in your vehicle at all times. Please call 810-648-2164 ext. 07 after you park in the designated Outpost parking spots on the west side of the building. When you call please tell us your name and how many in your family. You will then drive back to Outpost Food Pantry ramp and we will bring a box/bags of food/meat and put them in your trunk. Please stay healthy and safe. God Bless!!

SHS salutes its students and coaches for their performance in winning the 34th Annual Raymond T. Dunbar Jr. Sanilac County Academic Games! This is SHS’s 2nd consecutive title in these games and our 18th overall.

This was once again a true TEAM performance: the Social Studies team took 1st place, the Science and Math teams both took 2nd, and our ELA team took 3rd, just missing the final round by the slimmest of margins. Look for full team pictures once we return to school on Monday!

shared_text:
Sandusky MI Police Department
January 10 at 5:10 PM ·

On Friday January 10th the Sandusky Police Department was contacted by Sandusky Schools regarding a threats complaint. A voice message was left by a unknown male subject who sounded extremely intoxicated. Once this message was discovered, Sandusky Schools immediately contacted our agency. After the message was reviewed, Sandusky Police requested assistance from the Sanilac County Sheriffs Office road patrol division to provided extra security to all the schools.

During the investigation we obtained the phone number from where the call was made. Authorities in California were contacted and they are following up with the investigation. We believe the threat that was made to be unsubstantiated at this point but will continue to follow up closely with California authorities. We thank the staff, students, and parents for their patience and support.

shared_text:
Sandusky Junior/Senior High School
November 19, 2019 at 5:54 PM ·

Today SHS welcomed a team from CollegeBoard and Khan Academy. Our students and staff were able to share how Khan Academy and College Board influence opportunities at schools like SHS and offer suggestions for improvement. We are proud of our staff and students for showcasing their skills and talents to this national team of professionals.
